Conservation status.
Potamonautes perparvus
was listed as “least concern” ( IUCN 2003 ;
Cumberlidge et al . 2009
) because there is no evidence of a decline in the extent and quality of its habitat and there are no long-term threats to its habitat from disturbance and pollution (
Cumberlidge 2008 a
).

Distribution. This species is found in the tributaries of the Congo River and Lake Kivu drainage basins in the DR Congo and Rwanda (
Fig. 2
;
Table 2
).
